 href="Http://www.geocities.com/vsanthos/xicotl">Click here for the pictures...</a><br><br><br>Yes I know it was a big failure, and I'm sure a lot of people had more luck at lower levels, but, I had fun, and I felt like posting it, so nyah! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 4:34:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15128.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I came close to my Soulfire Hilt at 28...(kinda...)</span><hr size=1> I took in two groups, one for the lower throne room and garg room, and the other for the main Xic room.  Took us around five hours to get three hilts.  Average level was probably 35, and I'm sure now a days you could do it with one group 35'ish.  The big bonus though was all the MM granite.  I got atleast four pieces which was nice because I had a hard time getting them in groups, and I wanted my Ro bad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrilin31.showPublicProfile?language=EN>krilin31</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 6:58:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15128.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I came close to my Soulfire Hilt at 28...(kinda...)</span><hr size=1> MUA HA HA HA HA! The castle mistmoore.  I remember it well.  My first raid ever.  It was to get my guild leader his hilt.  lol.  First raid experience, first raid wipeout experience(s).  I say experiences because we had 2 complete wipe outs.  Anyway, those screenshots get me all mistyeyed of that certain &quot;nothing you do can save you from death&quot; feeling you get when you LoH, and /bow to the 5295723 mobs whailing on you before you switch to 3rd person view and watch your life sucked from the bar.  It's one of the few zones I've found that still give that feeling since orc hill.  Of course our last raid on spectres in oasis where we decided to do some deepwater gobbies during downtime was pretty mind-torturing fun.  AoE isn't a good idea in this place.... RUN TO ZONE.... I mean, SWIM FOR SHORE! lol.  <br><br>Avethar Soulforge &lt;Winds of Time&gt;<br>33 High Elf Paladin<br>Bertoxxulous server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uralandzvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RalandzVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 7:22:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15128.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I came close to soulfire...</span><hr size=1> Dieing with mana is inexcusable. ;P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulironvsanthos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liron Vsanthos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 1:56:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15128.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I came close to soulfire...</span><hr size=1> Yah, if I had used my mana, we would have both lived and killed him, my 29hp heal is just friggin uber!<br><br>And, conveniently for me, I left out the pics of me failing to taunt the deathly herald off of Draxis. =)<br><br>Te he he he<br><br>Anyways, that whole fight once Xicotl was pulled, took about 35 seconds, but I still think it was some of the best fun I've had in EQ so far, it's up there with doing the Ghoulbane quest, which, even more conveniently, was able to be done at level 20 thanks to my druid pal there, and took no time, because of him, as well.<br><br>Oh well, glad I could bring at least one person memories with this, other than that it's just a post I made because I can! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=15128.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=15128.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15128.topic&index=4><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=15128.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=15128.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15128.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgen